<HEADLINE>
800,000 people gathering for mass in Krakow for John Paul II: 
police
= (PICTURE) =
ATTENTION - UPDATES crowd figure ///
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
KRAKOW, Poland, April 7
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some 800,000 people were 
gathering Thursday in a vast field on the edge of the southern 
Polish city of Krakow for a mass in memory of Pope John Paul II, a 
police spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
"We estimate there are almost 800,000 faithful at the moment, 
but people continue to fill up the Blonia esplanadae," said police 
spokeswoman Sylwia Bober.
</P>
<P>
Krakow, in southern Poland, in the city where Karol Wojtyla 
lived for 40 years of his adult life before being elected pope in 
1978.
</P>
